 title: "The Last Ferry to Kisumu",
 content:
"Dickens Omondi stood at the rusted railing of the ferry, watching the hyacinth choke the shoreline. He had promised his village compatriots he would return the family's ancestral shield to the village, a relic stolen during the colonial era and recently recovered from a London auction house. The box was heavy in his hands. A storm was brewing over the lake, turning the water a violent grey. Beside him, a young Luo boy named Ochieng was fishing with a piece of twine. 'The water is angry today, Jaduong,' Ochieng said. Dickens nodded. 'It knows what I am carrying.' As the waves rose, rocking the boat violently, Dickens realized the shield wasn't just metal and hide; it was a conduit for history. He wasn't just crossing a lake; he was crossing a century of silence.",
 genre: "Drama",
 author: "Dickens Omondi",
