 content:
"Lil Dikie, an aspiring rapper from Eastlands, finally got his shot: a live performance at the biggest club in Westlands. He had spent his rent money on a gold chain that turned his neck green. The moment he stepped on stage, the DJ played a Benga track instead of his trap beat. Panic set in. Instead of rapping, Lil Dikie started aggressively dancing the Odi dance to the Benga rhythm. The crowd, confused at first, went wild. He didn't say a single word into the mic, but by morning, he was trending as the 'Mute King of Benga.' He retired from rap immediately.",
