"Sir Dickens was a man of logic, a retired physics professor. But logic failed him when he saw the creature coiled around the geothermal vents in Naivasha. It was a dragon, but its scales were made of obsidian and it breathed steam, not fire. A team of Chinese engineers, led by Mei Ling, were trying to contain it. 'It feeds on the earth's heat,' Mei shouted over the roar. Sir Dickens calculated the pressure variance. 'If you trap it, the Rift explodes,' he yelled back. 'We have to let it fly.' Together, they deactivated the containment field. The obsidian beast shot into the stratosphere, leaving the smell of sulfur and a silent understanding between an old teacher and a young engineer.",
