 id: 20,
 title: "Betrayal in Mombasa",
 content:
"Fatima ran a shipping logistics firm. Her brother, Yusuf, was her partner. When a shipment of illegal ivory was found in one of their containers, Fatima was arrested. She sat in the interrogation room, claiming innocence. Then the police played a recording. It was Yusuf, selling her out to the cartel to clear his gambling debts. The look on Fatima's face wasn't anger; it was pure, shattering heartbreak. She signed the confession to protect her brother, even though she knew the truth. A sister's sacrifice.",
